5 shall direct the secretary of the county election board in each
6 county to conduct a post-election audit following elections held on
7 dates set forth in Sections 1-101, 1-102, 1-103, and 20-101 of this
8 title.
9 B. The method, timing, and procedures for conducting a post-
10 election audit shall be determined by the Secretary of the State
11 Election Board.
12 C. The secretary of a county election board shall report the
13 findings of a post-election audit to the Secretary of the State
14 Election Board, and such report shall be available to the public.
15 D. The Secretary of the State Election Board may promulgate
16 policies, rules, and procedures to implement the requirements of
17 this section.
18 E. For the purposes of this title, a “post-election audit” is
19 defined as means a manual or electronic examination of a limited
20 number of ballots by a secretary of a county election board or other
21 authorized election officials following an election. A post-
22 election audit shall be conducted only at the direction of the
23 Secretary of the State Election Board and only subject to the
